# Yulin Zhang, 2026.1.23

This folder contains snakenake workflows for benchmarking TRACE in simulation models (TRACE manuscript Supplementary Section S2 - S3).

Folders:
- config -- configuration files for snakemake
- data -- simulation models and method executables
- workflow -- .smk files and python scripts used in workflows

## Before running and testing:

(1) Build `cython` extensions

To compile cython dependancies used in the workflow (assuming `cythonize` is appropriately linked from the environment):

```
cd trace_benchmark/workflow/scripts
cythonize -i -a -3 trace_utils.pyx
```

This should create a `*.so` library that contains utility functions that are of use.
------------

Note: if you get error of numpy head file could not be found like the following

```
/Users/zhangyulin/Desktop/github/research/ghost_admixture_hmm/arg_hmm/arg_hmm_utils.c:1099:10: fatal error: 'numpy/arrayobject.h' file not found
 1099 | #include "numpy/arrayobject.h"
      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1 error generated.
```

You could run before `cythonize`

```
export "CFLAGS=-I/Users/zhangyulin/mambaforge/envs/ghost_admix_hmm/lib/python3.11/site-packages/numpy/core/include/ -O3"
```

which you need to change the path to specify numpy header files in your environment.
------------

(2) Edit config files

Please check out config/config.yaml file.

Under "analyses", we listed out all analyses this workflow would run. One could specify "True" or "False" to specify the part of analyses they want to run.

Under "paths", we specifed a list of paths to program executables and directories to put the workflow outputs in. Please edit the paths to run the workflow on your machine.

## Testing:

To test if the workflow could be run with no error, one could try running

```
cd trace_benchmark
snakemake --dry-run
```

Potential errors:
1. "could not import trace_util" -- Please build cython extentions as suggested above
2. "Missing Input Exceptions"
    -- Please check if you've edited the "config.yaml" file correctly, specify "False" for all analyses that you are not running.
    -- Please check if you've include the correct .smk file to run (and mark out unrelated .smk file) at the end of "Snakefile".
